  "title": "Operations Executive - Project Logistics",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities will largely depend on the employee’s capacities but include (or may include) :</p><p>•\tExpertise in multimodal transport (road, air, sea), heavy-lift planning, and yard operations.</p><p>•\tTo ensure timely invoicing to customers</p><p>•\tPlan and coordinate logistics for project cargo including heavy lift and oversized shipments and review customer’s freight requests and select appropriate carrier</p><p>•\tPrepare and verify shipping documentation (commercial invoice, packing list, bill of lading, export declarations).</p><p>•\tEnsure compliance with international trade regulations and safety standards.</p><p>•\tMonitor cargo handling, loading/unloading, and secure transportation.</p><p>•\tNegotiate rates with carriers and vendors to optimize cost efficiency.</p><p>•\tManage project logistics budgets and track expenses.</p><p>•\tResolve operational issues promptly and implement contingency plans.</p><p>•\tProvide regular status updates and reports to management and clients.</p><p>•\tAbility to manage under pressure, coordinate multiple stakeholders, and deliver against tight schedules.</p><p>•\tCritical in maintaining continuity and minimizing non-productive time</p><p>•\tAny adhoc duties that assigned by Managers.</p><p><br />Requirement:<br />•\tMinimum Higer Nitec /Diploma / Degree in Supply Chain Management, Logistics or equivalent.<br /><br />•\t2 - 3 years of relevant working experience.</p><p>•\tExperience in freight forwarders & handling oversized cargoes</p><p>•\tWell verse with International Commercial Terms (INCOTERMS)</p><p>•\tAble to adapt to change of environmental policies and company policies</p><p></p>",
